---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Justin Doone"
  description="Marketing strategist working with investment firms and complex B2B teams. Background, approach, and how I work."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 pt-20 md:pt-32 pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">About</p>
    <h1 class="heading-display text-5xl md:text-7xl text-ink mb-10 leading-[0.95]">
      I help investment firms and complex B2B teams turn complicated products into clear stories.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-6">
      I'm based in Toronto and currently lead marketing operations for an asset manager. Before that I ran integrated campaigns for a handful of investment firms and a couple of consumer brands working to expand internationally.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
      Clients have included <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Greybrook Capital</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Clifton Blake</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Roxborough Communities</strong>, and a few consumer brands at the expansion stage.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mt-6">
      On a given day the job might mean writing copy, building a dashboard, or working through compliance edits. I do the work hands-on, not at arm's length from it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW I WORK -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 py-16 rule-top">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">How I work</p>
    <div class="space-y-8 text-ink-soft leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p>
        Most marketing problems are diagnostic before they're tactical. I want to understand the audience and what they need to believe before designing anything. If you skip that step, the rest of the campaign is just trying to fix it in execution.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work from one narrative and adapt it across whatever channels are involved. Most channel plans turn into nine campaigns saying nine slightly different things. The result is a content calendar with strategic ambitions.
      </p>
      <p>
        I do the measurement work myself. SQL, dashboards, attribution arguments. If I can't tell reach and revenue apart after a campaign, I'm not really doing the job.
      </p>
      <p>
        In regulated industries, the best work is the work that gets through compliance on the first pass. I write to the line, not over it. That's usually the difference between launching this quarter and launching whenever legal gets to it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 py-16 rule-top">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Get in touch</p>
    <h2 class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink mb-8">
      If you have something complicated to sell, I can probably help.
    </h2>
    <a
      href="mailto:hello@justindoone.com"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-ink text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent transition-colors"
    >
      hello@justindoone.com
      <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
